  <entry>
    <title>Limit the memory usage in Windows 10 WSL2</title>
    <link href="https://lydiazly.github.io/2022-07-16-Limit-memory-usage-in-Windows-10-WSL2"/>
    <id>https://lydiazly.github.io/2022-07-16-Limit-memory-usage-in-Windows-10-WSL2</id>
    <published>2022-07-16T06:56:11.000Z</published>
    <updated>2022-07-16T06:56:11.000Z</updated>
    
    
    <summary type="html">&lt;h2 id=&quot;limit-the-memory-usage&quot;&gt;Limit the memory usage&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&#39;s very annoying that WSL2 was always eating up my poor RAM. There
is a solution. It&#39;s working, except that the memory usage can&#39;t be
exactly &#39;limited&#39; but &#39;fixed&#39;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My distribution is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;line-numbers language-powershell&quot; data-language=&quot;powershell&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-powershell&quot;&gt;&gt; wsl &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;l &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;v
  NAME            STATE           VERSION
&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; Ubuntu-18&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;04    Running         2&lt;span aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; class=&quot;line-numbers-rows&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a configure file named &lt;code&gt;.wslconfig&lt;/code&gt; in your user
directory in Windows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open PowerShell as Administrator, shutdown your WSL2 and edit the
file:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;line-numbers language-powershell&quot; data-language=&quot;powershell&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-powershell&quot;&gt;&gt; wsl &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;--&lt;/span&gt;shutdown
&gt; notepad &lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;token variable&quot;&gt;$env&lt;/span&gt;:USERPROFILE\.wslconfig&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; class=&quot;line-numbers-rows&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For me the content is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;[wsl2]
memory=2GB
swap=0&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
